caption: What does this place not have!? My family and I happened into this restaurant randomly after our original reservation had gotten cancelled, and we are so happy it did! Right from the start we were greeted by the lovely and knowledgable staff about the food and drink options. For the beer lovers in your life this place is a must. The food, ambiance, and staff are all so welcoming and kind. Whether we had a request for more of their delicious grilled bread with the amazing mussels we ordered, or a staff member being kind enough to go through the playlist they were playing to give us the exact name of a song we like that played earlier that night (he went off the hummed beat, and got it right!). Their lovely staff is just one of the plethora of reasons to go back, it's just gilding the lily that they also have fair prices, EXCELLENT food, and delicious drinks.  I'm so excited to go back! this place is now held to the highest regard in my family as our favorite restaurant in Portland!
Very good prices.

I forgot the name of the waiter that served our table. HE WAS THE BEST. The service was excellent. So many variety of cocktails, beer and drinks. Food was delicious and homey. The vibe of the restaurant was stepping into someone’s fancy home.
Quite, cozy date night place! Server was awesome, with a great personality. Food was delicious...try the fried chicken platter = AMAZING! Good service + good food is an A++++ rating in my book.
Very clean. Had a great time. Great food
5 stars. Deliciously fresh seafood. The fish literally flaked when I picked it up with the fork. The batter was light and crispy. The mussels were wonderful. Even the fries were crisp to perfection.

We went there for a quick stop and the food was really nice and fresh. The fish and chips was amazing, the fish was well cook and really smooth. We took also the chowder, also nice and tasty. The lemonade was excellent, not so sweet and with a real lemon tast that was perfect.
Great beer selection and very friendly staff.

Have to give the staff 5 stars for a positive attitude working in the 45 degree rain. They were all pleasant and helpful. The chickpea patty melt was good, chicken a little dry,  the shared bites cheese platter, beets and fries were all okay.

Visited the East Ender late in the afternoon on a Sunday. They weren’t offering their regular menu until 5pm so we ordered from what seemed like their bar snacks menu. Made the best of it and the food was really good. We got fries, the fried chicken platter, and their selection of artisanal cheeses. Definitely suggest the thrice cooked fries!

Out of this world food and top notch service! It was my first time there but I am already planning my next visit. We had the stew, mussels, gnocchi, beets, cheese plate and thrice fried fries. Oh and the sea salt caramel dessert!!?? To die for!!! Wish I could give more then 5 stars!!

An amazing restaurant, all of the wait staff were so kind and welcoming and helpful. Outdoor seating was plentiful and everything was wiped down to follow COVID preparedness guidelines. The mussels were amazing and the plum ice cream for dessert is still on my mind. Definitely recommend
Really enjoyed the Tunisian stew and chowder. Good service!
Nice place, friendly people

Staff is extremely friendly! Stopped in for dinner and drinks. I got the burger and lemon drop. Burger was good. Wasn’t blown away, but good if you’re in the mood for a burger. Drinks were amazing. Would recommend if you’re in the area.

*Review for drinks only*  The sit-down tables are for dining only, but they do have these huge barrels and a few seats if you are just grabbing drinks (aka if you are waiting forever for Duckfat and need to kill some time). Our party of five was able to grab one of these barrels on a Sunday at around 8.  I had the Bee's Knees cocktail, which I think was some kind of vodka and honey concoction (not very memorable), which was too sweet for my taste. So if you like sweet cocktails, you will love East Ender. Otherwise just stick to beer or wine.
Yum. The food was great. The staff was beyond wonderful. The vibe was fun and chill. Lovely little place. Appreciate the attention to detail with cool plates and nice cocktails.
Excellent food

Creative touch to stardard fare - burger with blister pepper and Sesame bun with a smoky tinge. Hake chowder (for those who want to part from lobster bisque for one day at least) is full of hake, light on cream and rather unique offering in a state of lobsters. And side order of beets Is fresh and generous in portion and delightful. And service is swift and friendly. Couldn't ask for more in a town that is rebranding itself for the foodies and art and culture seekers

Drinks were AMAZING but the food was just pretty good. Definetly would come back for cocktails!! Staff is super kind and accommodating. They have some outdoor space under a tent for extra covid spacing. We had a lovely time, thanks so much!

Everything we had was delicious, including fish & chips, Caesar salad, pork sandwich, and the lobster roll.  Outdoor dining setup was really nice and felt safe for COVID.  Server was warm and helpful.
Food was hit or miss, but the portions were just too small for what they charge.
Amazing food, terrific staff, beautiful location. An instant new favorite!

Great experience here! Service was wodnerful and food as well. Would definitely come back next time we are in town. There was also a cocktail I couldn’t get enough of that has gin and  chartreuse in it. We brought our dog and they were so friendly to him and provided a dog bowl.
The mixologist! This guy loves his craft! The drinks were amazing..get them how they’re made. The staff are friendly too! Didn’t get a chance to grab a bite, next time! Cheers!
Delicious food, excellent service in spacious outdoor space.
Decent enough to get a drink whilst waiting for a table at Eventide. The wings were too cooked and dry
Weather was perfect to dine outside and have a drink. Great staff.

Why...Did...I...Come...Here, I have been sitting here, waiting and wondering if anyone is going to show up with the drink I ordered over 15 minutes ago. While on the subject of losing my patience, I came here because I was hungry, not to sit here debating on if I'm actually going to get my order taken before closing time. I wouldn't wish this service even on the man who killed my mother. PLEASE stay away from this establishment, there are plenty of good eateries near by with employees that will at least acknowledge your presence in their restaurant. Absolutely Disgusted, Chillidoe
Great food, great service, a must-go place in Portland

Stopped in on Sunday after walking into town from the Eastern Prom, thinking that the outdoor seating was for the Duckfat restaurant. Ordered a beey salad and the fish & chips to split. The beet salad was excellent, with pepita's and a white cheese (can't remember exactly) with balsamic dressing, but it was the fish & chips that really stood out. The chips were fine, but the fish was superb, very flavorful and the crust was perfect, crispy and flakey, and not soggy in the least. When the bill came, we realized that we weren't at Duckfat at all, but at The East Ender. Turns out that their outside seating areas are close together, and we weren't the first to make the mistake. The waitress was super gracious about it and explained that while the two restaurants were wholly separate, they had a good and cooperative relationship. In short it was a very pleasant visit for an excellent mid-day snack, and we'll put it on the list for a full meal some day when normal dining resumes.
Great food and good outdoor setup during covid. Would definitely recommend.
The drink selection is great and the food is even better. The mussels are a definite must have.

This is one of the many gems in Portland. They do a wonderful dinner, but it is one of my favorite lunch spots when I have time to dine in. Their menu is updated often, but there is always something delicious. It's been a while since I have seen/had their trout fritters, but I love those things. Their burger is tasty. The dinners I have had there are also delicious. I remember a pork and grits that was wonderful. The cocktails are also really tasty and crafted well. There servous is always friendly and attentive.
Lovely, cozy place with comfortable old-school booths. Menu is very good and not slave to trends.  The scallops were the best I've ever tasted!
Solid plates and drinks
Great apps and beer selection!
Very good meals.Service a little slow. Very comfortable place and easy for talking.
Nice spot for lunch. Good food. Didn’t disappoint.
Cozy feel, amazing service, mussels were just ok
delicious brussel sprouts, great service, but the non alcoholic beer is still 5%
Hidden gem for sure, and dare I say it, the fries are way better than Duck Fat!
Great Burger 👍 and bartenders, Best Burger in town.

I hate to review this place because I think it's such a gem... I want it all to myself! Good beer and wine selection, fantastic service, and a small but special menu of dishes they do REALLY well. You can't go wrong with anything on the menu, but my favorites are their grilled chicken tikka and fish & chips. My favorite thing about East Ender is that it feels special and intimate without being overly priced... hard to come by in Portland these days!
Great staff and very accommodating for allergies.
Great food and atmosphere! Service was fantastic and accommodating for 8 people with small children.
Incredibly great service, cozy environment, and a smart selection of libations keeps East Ender a top spot to check into!

Really nice cozy place, the brick walls give it a nice rustic feel. The food is amazing, super fresh, delicious combinations. Servers were courteous and always on!  Definitely recommended for couples or families.
Nice place for warm food on a winter afternoon.

Very good food and beer, but overpriced. Hard to understand justification for the prices for a burger and skirt steak. I only go because my wife likes the food. Many other places in Portland to eat with as good quality but a lot less cost. Shop around.
Went for brunch. Pleasant waitstaff and tasty food. Good drinks options too!

A favorite place for... I think about a decade now for my husband and I. While the restaurant adjacent to this one is amazing, we always like to giggle at each other and do a little high five while people starve outside in line next door LOL
The waitress was wonderful but food was average.  The risotto was not as creamy as it could have been and not a lot of lobster.
Head great drinks and awesome food, was a great relaxing meal.
Great thrice fried potatoes!!
We came in after not being able to get a table at Duckfat and were not sorry. They were accommodating of our baby, had lovely ambiance, and an excellent menu and great service.

My first time dining at East Ender was great but sadly the second time didn't live up to the expectations. I'm not sure if it was a mistake or a poor recipe but the risotto was flavorless! The dish consisted of watery rice with chunks of lobster and pea pods - completely devoid of any broth, flavor, cheese, milk, or seasoning. The rest of our food was good but the risotto spoiled an otherwise nice experience.

We stopped in for lunch. Friendly servers and good atmosphere, but the food was mediocre at best. The “thrice cooked” fries were clearly just dipped back into the fryer to heat up after sitting for awhile. There are other better options nearby.
Awesome mixologists! Get the "wink and a nod" drink. It's amazing. Great staff and service
Great food nice environment and God service.  The menu is fantastic it's definitely worth a try if you're local or visiting.
Good food

Quick, friendly service.  Great location! Street parking.  Order: Happy Hour CHICKEN LEG RILLETTES WITH HOUSE MUSTARD & PICKLES $7: this was so good! Especially loved the way the bread was prepared.  FRIED FISH SANDWICH $13: delicious, lite, refreshing & filling. Salad was not drenched in dressing but could be a little less salty.  The pickles were a highlight with each dish. They were very sweet!
Fantastic burger and good beer selection
Cute and quaint.  Really small, though.
Rachel the bartender was awesome.  We enjoyed her talent and her recommendations.  We will be back!
Wonderful food and fantastic cocktails in a cozy, upscale setting.
Excellent food and service
Excellent service & delicious food.
Really good spot with convenient on street parking. Had the Braised Pork Shoulder,  it was nice and tender. They have good drinks, good beer selection and reasonable price. Check them out.
Very cozy well decorated atmosphere. Food was excellent. Went for brunch, had duck confit and breakfast sandwich, both were great! Highly recommend this place
Great brussel sprouts, outdoor seating, and service

We had a wonderful experience eating here! Great Bloody Mary’s and their eggs in purgatory is top five meals I’ve ever had (pictured below). Cody the bartender is an awesome guy and makes some incredible drinks! Highly recommend this place to anyone stopping in Portland!
Friendly place. Great food!

Food was good and drinks were strong. Good atmosphere but could be cleaner but nothing that stopped us from eating there. The downside is the price and wait. Waited over half an hour for a burgwr and chicken sandwich. Paid $100 dollars for three drinks, small snack, burger with fries and chicken sandwich with salad.
Not bad. Not my favorite but some  creativity. Would try something different going back to see if it pays off a little more.
Great food. Really nice location. Excellent drinks. Not too pricey
Tasty and delicious creations!  Fabulous sandwiches and the Brussels sprouts are acidic and mouth watering. Lovely place!
Great food and the burger is incredible.  Im generally underwhelmed by burgers at restaurants but this was among the best i've had.
Great place!
Great food and friendly staff in a cozy spot. It seems like they pick up a lot of the overflow from Duckfat, but people should make this a destination in it's own right.
The staff was incredibly friendly and helpful!
Great entrées that range from seafood to chickpeas. Pleasantly surprised. Nice waiting staff, too.

We walked in because the wait in nearby restaurant was too long. It was a mistake. My lobster risotto barely had any lobster and it wasn't risotto, just over cooked rice. The burger lacked salt, was falling apart, and was tasteless.

Located right next to DuckFat, East Ender has surprisingly less folks. So if in doubt whether you will be able to grab a table during rush hour or lunch, don't fret - they will likely be able to accommodate you. I'd highly recommend trying chicken wings in lime rub and brussel sprouts - these both were really impressive appetizers!!!
Fast, friendly service and delicious food! They also have a Temperance drink menu so you can have something non-alcoholic.
Get the hamburger
Amazing flavor and creative menu

Came here because the wait was long at Eventide. Omg how happy were we that we ended up here. The atmosphere was much more relaxed and the staff was super friendly. Also the FOOD was AMAZING! We had the fish and chips and gnocchi... both were creative dishes that tasted delicious!!

A 15 minute wait quickly turned into 30 despite several four-tips open, and our waters were never refilled. The food was fine, but this really seems like a place just to have a beer while you wait to be seated next door at Duckfat.

Place is underrated since its next to Duckfat.  I would highly suggest this place due to the ambience and really great menu.  I had some of the best muscles here and Gnochii.  They have a great selection of beers and cocktails on top if it.

The food was amazing. The portions are a bit small, but the prices are tough to beat for such high quality food in Portland. We had our kids with us, they do have pasta or grilled cheese for the kids meals. Mine both got the grilled cheese and ate EVERYTHING on their plates, which is not normally the case. The pork was tender and incredibly flavorful. And definitely get the fried Brussels sprouts! We will definitely be going back!
The grilled cheese are amazing. Good beer selection.

Our third time eating here and still as great as the first.  Awesome beer selection and a nice assortment of food options.  I went with the smoked burger last time and it was delicious.  This time, I got the grilled chicken tikka sandwich and it was even better.  So good - will be back again next time!
Overstar....by half. Food ehhh service was very hospitable. Late lunch and in between shifts. Thank you for the drinks....

GREAT staff. Our waitress was phenomenal. Attentive and helpful. The food was wonderful, and do not miss the thrice fried fries. They were crispy and well seasoned. The menu is a bit limited, but available online so you can check it out beforehand if you have any concerns!!
So delicious!
Nice place good food
Secretly one of the best restaraunts in Portland...so.good.
Best mussels ever had great food
Very nice.  Cold rainy mid-May day.  I'll admit we only came over for a beer while we waited for our table next door but I will be back.  Looked like really good food.
Not good.we were told to come in at 11 and there would no problem getting a table for 2.when we showed up.we were told a 2 hour wait. I won't go back

One of the best restaurants I have ever been to! Amazing food and a great atmosphere. We got the cesar salad, braised pork shoulder, grits and fried brussel sprouts. The salad was perfectly dressed, the meat was cooked really well. The atmosphere was perfect for a romantic but somewhat casual date, cozy low light with a rustic Maine look.
Interesting menu options and some good fallbacks like burgers. Service staff was friendly  knew the menu.  Nice rustic atmosphere.
Great food. Amazing dessert.  Awesome staff!
Quaint with excellent and reasonably priced food.
Great food.  Friendly staff.

We made a reservation for a late lunch on a Saturday in February. They had our reservation and after a little wait, sat us at a table (the room was empty) and then we waited and waited and waited. My in-laws were not happy waiting, so we told them thank you but we're not staying. This second time we took a friend who we were visiting in Portland, as she loves this restaurant. Again, we had a long wait just for someone to see we were waiting at the door. Then there was a lot of communication issues, but about what I don't know. We finally decided to just go sit at the bar. And had a great experience with Cody! He took great care in our drink prep (loved the Lemon Ginger Drop) and got our meals ordered and without too long we were enjoying our dinners. Pappardelle, Chicken Salad and a Burger. I'm not sure why there are communication issues with whoever is supposed to run front of the house. We've never been upstairs either. I just think with all the competition in Portland of fabulous places to eat, they should think about this detail.
I really enjoyed the atmosphere here, and our food was absolutely delicious. Good service and good drink selection too - definitely recommend!
Next door to duck fat, very good neighbors
Great service unique delicious food and selection for lunch service. Extensive drink menu eclectic and atmosphere friendly!

A small eatery good for a quick, satisfying meal. Menu is concise, making selection easy. Decent beer and wine options. Service was rushed, which was strange on a winter Monday night with low traffic.

We loved this restaurant. Great vibe, interesting and tasty drinks made with local homemade syrups. Yummy! We both had the burger. Who knew smoked hamburger was so delicious! Recommend medium well though if you don't want any red juices! Great music. Spencer was our bartender - top notch!!

Hearty, rich meals, great prices, cozy atmosphere.  We loved the gnocchi with mushrooms and also the spicy pappardelle. A side of perfectly prepared, savory roasted brussel sprouts. The wine list is small but varied, and there are a few great local beers as well.  There is a full bar with interesting cocktails, though we didn't sample any.  We will go back for sure.
Ok
Try the Asian slaw
Amazing restaurant that we stumbled upon. Food, drinks, service and atmosphere is an A+
Really Good food and drinks but small selection for the price.  Still a place I'd come back to for a special night
Nice burgers and fries. Bit pricey but hey, it's Portland.
Often overlooked as it's located nextdoor to well-known Duck Fat... East Ender had a great menu & drinks - I prefer the fries here to their neighbor's.
The Maine lobster and mushrooms grit was sooo delicious! The place is cozy and the staff are very friendly.
Small intimate place great for lunch or dinner. Really good food!
Im not one of those fancy smancy food critics that takes reviews too seriously, I just know a good soup when I taste one and a good beer selection when I see one. Trust me.
Cozy place to enjoy some local food. Nothing fancy but all the food was great. Good drink options and friendly service.
Great place
Their happy hour was phenomenal. We walked in because the place next door had a crazy wait. We were upset we didnt go in here straight off the bat. Great service and prices. Would definitly go back.
Amazing bar staff.
Awesome service, everything was delicious. Get the warmed olives and chicken wings.
Interesting menu... friendly staff...very eager to please...
Five 🌟 minus my experience with the pretzel. Very small and they put celery salt in the mustard.
Excellent chilli and lime chicken wings. Spaghetti squash went remarkably well with hake fish and chips. Thrice cooked fries were fantastic, but have them hot for maximum effect.
Very allergy conscious, courteous, and timely service. Excellent food! Well worth revisiting!
Amazing food and super friendly service! Everything on the menu looks delicious!
Very good food and friendly staff. Our entrees were awesome. The dessert was not quite as good but still very good.
A really relaxed and wonderful evening & great dinner.  Enjoyed this nice booth seating overlooking the Portland Harbor
Grabbed a few drinks during their Saturday happy hour (!!!) Great menu, nice strong drinks, and even nicer staff. They even use paper & bamboo straws instead of plastic!
First time back in 2 years.  Menu more complicated than before but good, and slightly more expensive.

Sat at the bar twice on one weekend. They had a decent beer selection and the food was good. They are close by to Duck Fat and Eventide, don’t let the crowds in front of those places cloud your judgement, this is a great spot as well that is much easier to get into.

The waitress so clearly hated us. She hid the happy hour menu from us (we came in well within the window) and was very annoyed when we asked for it. The thrice cooked fries are over complicating something that’s easy, and they are not worth eating. The burger was pretty solid, though it would be better with tomato and lettuce. Guess they’re going for a simple vibe. Drinks were pretty good! I think this could’ve been a better experience with a server that didn’t hate us. I wonder what we did. She should talk to management if she doesn’t like the specials.

Came in 5 minutes before lunch was over; they were so nice and got our order in. We were starving and ordered several options. Everything was amazing, they didn’t rush us instead they chatted with us about the day.
Awesome drinks, friendly staff.
Grilled cheese w/mushrooms a true delight!

The food that they had was ok. The staff was friendly enough. We were told we couldn't get scrambled eggs because the chef doesn't like to make scrambled eggs, we were informed they were out of one thing when we tried to order, then after our order was taken the waiter came back and told us they only had 2 of one item and one of another, so only one person in our party actually got what they wanted. Also the food selection wasnt really that great. The homemade doughnut was pretty good though.
Amazing burgers, cool space, great cocktails and beer selection.
Great atmosphere!
Good food and service.
Stopped in for cocktails, absolutely delicious. Wish we hadn't made dinner reservations elsewhere. Will be back for sure

Nice ambiance, simple menu, staff was friendly.  Only complaint was that I ordered the gnocchi and it was SO salty, almost inedible because of the amount of salt even though the rest of the ingredients were really good.  Also just be aware that the portion sizes are quite small.
Amazing service at the bar upstairs with Jeff!  Great cocktails and the food is so good. Well worth a visit!

We stumbled upon this cute restaurant by accident and are very happy about it! We arrived around 8:30PM and were still gracefully seated near the window by the lovely host/server. They have an extensive drink menu and a smaller food menu, but it has something for everyone. Most of the food came from local farms and businnesses so it’s a great way to support those and have a lovely meal!
Excellent food, good wine and great service!
Great atmosphere. Friendly and knowledge staff. Delicious menu. Excellent beer, wine and coctail selection
Great food

4 &1/2 stars. Dishes were interesting and well prepared.  The service was very good, prompt, polite and accurate.  We we're brought deep fried bacon as a complimentary appetizer, which was actually the least "appetizing" food on the table.

I had an amazing meal here of lobster risotto, that was rich and creamy and full of lobster meat. The chefs really prepare  some amazing dishes and specials.  They have a fun drink menu and serve some really delicious concoctions. The food is to rave about but be prepared to spend the money.

Went with two other couples and was pleasantly surprised at how strong the menu is as well as the prices for the entrées.  They have a small bar and small dining area both upstairs and downstairs. We sat near the door and every time the door open it was a little on the chilly side for people closest to the door.  The service was exceptional and the food was delicious. Can be a little challenging down in this neck of the old port...But definitely worth finding and enjoying.  Will definitely be coming back!
Duck confit Benedict was delicious. Service wasn't great but I hope it was just a bad day.
Love The Last Word Cocktail and the two outdoor tables in the summer.
Funky downtown eatery
Great new restaurant
Great burger!

Nice little restaurant. The staff is very nice and friendly. I recommend making reservations as it is on the small side and can get busy at times. The food is good but it is not very filling. It is also on the expensive side. I recommend going at least once to try it!
High quality gourmet food, relaxed and hip atmosphere
My 12 year old son review of the lobster melt was AWESOME.  Both of my sons want to go back the next day for lunch.

overall really not impressed. lobster sandwich was extremely wet, mediocre flavor. beet salad was meh.  pork belly app was meh. only actually delicious thing on anyways plate was a piece of fried haddock that was fried to perfection. wouldn't return.
Solid cocktails, delicious food, friendly staff

An unexpected delight. We dropped in as a group of six on a Sunday afternoon and were told the kitchen was about to close. We were fortunate to have been not 10 minutes later, because each person in my party was greatly impressed by her entree! (I had the pork belly sandwich.) The service was good too.
One of our favorite spots! Interesting and delicious food, with great people. Always excellent service.

I've only been here for brunch but it was fantastic. I'd seen an amazing dish on the website that wasn't labeled and didn't seem to match anything on the menu so I ordered the duck hash (their signature). Turns out it was the dish on the website (!) and it was amazing. The hash part is done as more of a croquet/tater tot which adds an interesting texture and the squash it came with had a delightful orange zest in it. Very yum. Did not try any cocktails but the coffee was good
Amazing food. Wonderful staff. It's a good idea to make a reservation.
The food was to die for. The services was great. Definitely recommend East ender. If you are near by, or far away make your way here for some great food.
Have eaten there three times and food/service have been great each time. Bacon jelly in the house burger was awesome. Excellent tap list
Very tasty, nice beer and wine selection, a little pricey for lunch but quality of food made it worth it. Friendly service and no wait. Kids said we should come back :).

Had a pretty bad first experience. First off, some jerk douchey patron called me an idiot (per my significant other already inside) when I was looking down cleaning off my boots and missed the "use other door sign"  affixed to the window seven feet above ground, and commented on how I couldn't read. (To note, the correct door to use says "lounge upstairs" so it's a touch misleading, thinking that's the lounge door).  Slow service. There are six tables. We were the latest of four taken tables total (mostly parties of two). Got ignored for the couple that came in after us, no big deal. Finally got order in. Waited on drinks. The party with jerkface was sat a short while afterwards, ordered wine, and server literally went to pour it right away. Still no drink. Asked again, it was obviously forgotten. Bloody Mary made with fish oil or something, so it was gross, unfortunately.  Seemed overwhelmed with the four tables, now adding a fifth, so the overall feel was just that we were an annoyance. Food was okay, nothing special. Fries and Brussels Sprouts were actually pretty good. We were there because of the long wait next door, and cold weather. Last time we'll make that decision.
Great happy hour!

5 of us had dinner this evening and enjoyed it very much. 2 burgers, 1 fish and chips, chickpea and chicken. Good selections of beer and drinks. Only negative is portion sizes are smaller than normal entrees and appetizers, all food was more like bar bite size. It was enough food but a bit pricey for portion size. Might go back..
Great cocktails and a truly special fish and chips!
Awesome mussels, they were huge.
The best smoked hake soup!
Solid meal, good place to go if you want something unique that feels traditional
Everything was amazing, especially the service! Laid-back but still felt very special.
One of my favorite restaurants in Portland.
Great atmosphere. Cool local spot, recommend he Lobster Melt!

Super friendly staff, delicious drinks, and incredible food. We were seated almost immediately, our server was so helpful and sweet, and the lobster melt was one of the top 5 best sandwiches I have ever had in my life.

Nice service, but it was freezing inside and our food took way way too long! We ordered immediately upon arriving and waited an hour + between ordering and actually getting served. The food itself was not my favorite- my boyfriend got the pork belly which was good but the cavatelli I ordered was hard and lacked flavor. Overall not the best experience.
Great fish and chips!
Been here twice for lunch while traveling in Maine on business. Strong menu, great flavors,  and food,  wonderful service. Today had a chowder that was fabulous. A sweet spot.
Great food and drinks at reasonable prices. Have to try the smoked pork belly. Burgers are awesome too.
The food was mediocre at best - service and ambiance were both good. We won't be returning.
Great drink specials
The wait staff was super friendly, professional and discreet. Our food was tasty and we were seated immediately, even without a reservation. Beer was good. I'd go again and recommend!
Very unique take on a Caesar salad. Delicious
Really good seafood and fries. The fries are AMAZING!
Very nice place.... great bartender upstairs, relaxed, cool wait staff, interesting bar snacks and apps. I had a wonderful time!
Not as many beer choices as I would have expected, but my fish was incredible. It was a little more expensive than I was hoping to find, but I wasn't disappointed in the quality.

Had a delicious meal here. The duck was outstanding as was the pasta with walnut pesto and mushrooms. The fish and chips was good, although I would have preferred it less deep fried. Drinks were excellent as was our server!
Great drinks downstairs AND upstairs. Folks who own and work there are nice. Food is very good. Everything from app to dessert is freshly prepared and delish.
The server was incredibly nice. The food was a feast for the eyes and stomach. I highly recommend the duck breast, pork belly, grilled octopus and trout.
Delicious lunch offering.
Hidden gem overshadowed by its neighbor.
Great food & drinks, nice atmosphere!

Venue: good ambiance and music, pretty hipster Staff: friendly and fast Food: good but not great value for the price Drinks: I got the cider one night and a lemon drop the next, both good Food Not pictured: soft pretzel: very small, nothing special Wings: very tasty rub and sauce Chili fries: tasty smoky pork chili  I wouldn't recommend it because for the price the food isn't that amazing and the drinks are not cheap. But if you are fine with the price, the food is not bad.

I thought the online menu was deceiving. If you're going to have a changing menu, you shouldn't post it online.  The service was excellent which was the only reason this place is getting stars.  Food was overpriced for the portion. I had the stew which had rice, garbanzo beans, 2 pieces of squash which were about 2.5x1.5x1.5 big, and two baby onions and the tiniest piece of chicken I've ever paid 5 dollar for. This meal totaled 17 dollars.
Great food at a great price. Had the chicken fried stake for brunch.

Not impressed..  the menu they have posted is not there menu any more, and when we asked the staff they said that was from last owner.. food was over priced and flavors where definitely not up to par.  Not a big option to pick from And Would never ever go back.

I have mixed feelings about this restaurant in its current incarnation.  On one hand, the food is very good, and I enjoy it.  As someone who's into veg/hybrid recipes, imagine my surprise that the tartare and burger are my favorite selections on the menu!  On the other, the service has been absolutely terrible, almost every time, in the 4 times we have been there.  Plus, you get the inevitable friends of the kitchen staff, at the bar, who distract the kitchen staff, and general lack of care in managing service and/or customer satisfaction, that make me want to go someplace else.  As someone who has worked in restaurants professionally, experiencing a restaurant that's MARGINAL, at best, service-wise, then seeing its staff congregated about the bar is a MAJOR turn off.  Does anyone manage this place?  I just spent 113 + tip at this restaurant.  I can spend the same at a number of other popular local restaurants, and receive far better service.  If this restaurant was smart or good on any level, they would have up settled us promptly on our chit, since on this an off night, and with the proper service for drinks and food, our base would have been 160+.  Ever wonder why other restaurants are killing it on a Wednesday, at peak time, when East Ender is practically empty?  Case closed.  You have to manage your service better, or you're done.

I went here with two other people for my birthday this past Monday. Honestly, I'm surprised there aren't more reviews?! It's a little small inside on the first floor, but cute. There is also an upstairs which is pretty large with nice views out the windows.  Maine lobster nachos and fried sweet potato w/ honey mustard = both awesome. Main entrees were awesome. The quality of everything was very high and we will definitely be going back.

Terrible experience!  The service was extremely slow. I ordered ribs and ended up with food poisoning.  My girlfriend's received a few small chunks of over cooked brisket.  On top of it all, my server added her own tip to the bill.  Last I knew that's considered theft.  I would avoid this place like the plague.
